-- Done:
-- =====
--  Internally a gTree uses two types of index:
--  A node index can be used to directly subscript the internal tree nodes.
--  A display index is semi-opaque in that it takes collapsed nodes into account, and
--  only has meaning when starting from the root to locate the corresponding node index.
--  A display index always has a value 1..1[+root[vnc]] and is ephemeral/never stored.

